Collophore. Anterior side with 14 chaetae, 8 proximal spine-like chaetae, 1 ciliated chaeta, 3 ciliated chaetae apically acuminate and 2 mac distally; posterior side with 9 chaetae, 5 spines, 3 thin ciliated chaetae and 1 smooth chaeta distally; lateral flap with about 17 chaetae, 5 smooth and 12 ciliated (
Fig. 43E
).

Furcula. Manubrium ventral formula with 1, 2 2, 2/4 (subapical), 12 (apical) ciliated chaetae of different sizes plus approximately 11 elongated apical scales per side (
Fig. 43F
); manubrial plate with 2 blunt mac ciliated abruptly acuminate at the apex, 4–5 ciliated chaetae of different sizes and 3 psp. Dens dorsally without blunt mac (
Fig. 43G
).
